Use the standard library
This is how to common of l1 and l2:
   Remember that result is []
   Remember that i is 0
   Do this l1's length times:
      Remember that x is item i in l1
      When x is in l2, then:
         When x is not in result, then:
            Add result to x
         End when
      End when
      Increase i
   End do
   Remember that result is bubble_sort of result
   The answer is result
Now you know
>>> common of [1, 4, 3, 34, 653, 2, 5] and [5, 7, 1, 5, 9, 653, 121] 
[1, 5, 653]
>>> common of [5, 3, 2, 8] and [3, 2] 
[2, 3]
>>> common of [1, 4, 3, 34, 653, 2, 5] and [5, 7, 1, 5, 9, 653, 121] 
[1, 5, 653]